---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Case Studies" description="Projects by Sorn Maksumic — Snapstock.app dividend platform and TibiaPVP.com game server.">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Case Studies</h1>
    <p class="text-slate-500 mb-10">Projects I've built and shipped.</p>

    <div class="space-y-6">
    <!-- Snapstock -->
    <div class="glass-card rounded-2xl overflow-hidden">
      <div class="p-6 sm:p-8">
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-start sm:justify-between gap-4 mb-6">
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-1">Snapstock.app</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-400">Dividend Stock Analysis Platform</p>
          </div>
          <a href="https://snapstock.app" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap">
            snapstock.app ↗
          </a>
        </div>

        <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Existing stock tools were too generic for dividend investing. So I partnered with 
          <strong class="text-white">Ryne Williams</strong> (~100K YouTube subs) to build a system 
          with a clear, repeatable framework — usable by beginners, but deep enough for serious analysis. 
          <strong class="text-white">1,800+ dividend investors</strong> use Snapstock to make clearer, 
          more consistent long-term investment decisions.
        </p>

        <div class="mb-6">
          <h3 class="text-xs font-semibold text-slate-600 uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mb-3">Technology</h3>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            {["Vue.js", "Java", "PostgreSQL", "REST API", "Financial Modeling Prep"].map(s => 
              <span class="px-2.5 py-1 bg-navy-800/30 border border-navy-700/30 text-slate-400 text-xs font-medium rounded-lg">{s}</span>
            )}
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xs font-semibold text-slate-600 uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mb-3">Features</h3>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-2">
            {[
              "Share price performance",
              "Snapscore: Company scoring",
              "Red flag detection",
              "Last 10-year / quarter charts",
              "REIT mode",
              "Watchlists",
              "ETF overlap analysis",
              "DCF calculator",
              "Financial statements",
              "News aggregation",
              "Screener"
            ].map(f => (
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-slate-400">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500 shrink-0" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
                {f}
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- TibiaPVP.com -->
    <div class="glass-card rounded-2xl overflow-hidden">
      <div class="p-6 sm:p-8">
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-start sm:justify-between gap-4 mb-6">
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-1">TibiaPVP.com</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-400">Private game server (pre-university project)</p>
          </div>
          <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm text-slate-600 whitespace-nowrap">
            tibiapvp.com (2017 — 2018)
          </span>
        </div>

        <p class="text-slate-400 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          My first real server project — before university. I ran a custom Tibia 7.4 
          private server on a <strong class="text-white">Linux</strong> dedicated server, using the real game map. 
          I modified the <strong class="text-white">C++ server source</strong>, wrote 
          <strong class="text-white">Lua scripts</strong> for custom game mechanics, and 
          used known reverse engineering techniques on the Windows 7.4 client, 
          including DLL injection, to build an anti-bot client. Players earned coins by killing each other to buy 
          custom weapons, armors, and spells.
        </p>

        <div class="mb-6">
          <h3 class="text-xs font-semibold text-slate-600 uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mb-3">Screenshots</h3>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
            {["A4EwMha.jpg", "AdwgyVP.png", "Afe5egx.jpg", "pJoifkU.png"].map(f => {
              const name = f.replace(/\.[^.]+$/, '');
              const ext = f.includes('.') ? f.split('.').pop() : '';
              return (
                <a href={`/images/tibia/${f}`} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="shrink-0">
                  <img src={`/images/tibia/${name}_thumb.${ext}`} alt={`TibiaPVP screenshot`} class="rounded-lg border border-navy-700/30 hover:border-indigo-500/50 transition-colors w-24 h-24 object-cover" />
                </a>
              );
            })}
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xs font-semibold text-slate-600 uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mb-3">Technology</h3>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            {["C++", "Lua", "Linux", "DLL Injection", "Reverse Engineering", "TCP/IP"].map(s => 
              <span class="px-2.5 py-1 bg-navy-800/30 border border-navy-700/30 text-slate-400 text-xs font-medium rounded-lg">{s}</span>
            )}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
